EditorData.AnimationTags: [Player] fails to reproduce the secret hand gesture. <Kealan>

Text.Value: I told you to leave. What happens next is your fault.
Here you go. Won't happen again.
Still, you went easy on Silfy even though you caught her in your pockets.
My gang says you've been messing with them. Don't deny it.
They're murderers. I'd spit in the eye of any god the likes of them worship.
There's nothing else to be said, for now.
This is our hideout, but hey, maybe you didn't know.
Suit yourself.
Not at all. You've got foresight - that'll help you to survive.
You idiot. What comes next is on you.
Well, look who's come to visit.
That's it. I'm telling the guards what you did. Everything you did!
Here's some free advice, more valuable than gold: don't bargain, just take.
Little slow on the uptake, aren't you?
Any reason you're still here?

EditorData.logicalname: Told to leave but still in hideout

Text.Value: I'm sure this was a misunderstanding. My things cost me a lot... I really need them back.
I go where I like - told you already. And I'll tell you again if I have to.
Leave.
I had a feeling you'd be back.
Well, it's been a pleasure. You know the way out.
Anything else?
You took advantage of Mattis.
Thanks. See you in Baldur's Gate, I hope. Now scram, before I get emotional.
Not sure why you're poking your nose in our business, though.
Why're you running all these schemes and swindles? Risky, you know.
Do you have anything to trade?
That ritual's nothing more than a fancy way to kick us out and leave us for dead.
Messing with our business, yeah?
You did this to yourself!
We have nothing to talk about.
I didn't touch the idol. Don't know what happened to it.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: The idol was moved out of the expected triggers, the player has it and tries to lie about it

Text.Value: Don't come back unless you want to talk business.
Damn it. Having that stashed away would have made life a lot easier.

EditorData.NodeContext: Frustrated, disappointed. Possible stamp of the foot on 'damn it'. Clenched fists.

Text.Value: You're about as intimidating as a flail snail in a salt mine.
Happy to help.
Okay, that's funny. You're funny.
Still, you've been a friend to us so far.
I'm not your mother. Do as you please.
I'm not your father. Do as you please.
I'm not your parent. Do as you please.
Sure. When we sell it in the city, I'll make sure you get your cut.
You'd better keep these kids in check. They won't get off so lightly forever.
That 'big shiny idol' is part of a sacred ritual. Don't you have any respect?
Copy the gesture.
You let that adventurer hit Meli.
Poking your nose in other people's business is the best way to get rich, I find.
Sure. Silfy probably grabbed them by mistake.

EditorData.NodeContext: Playing innocent. Silfy stole the items on purpose.

Text.Value: I'm not joining your little criminal gang.
And for that, you get one more chance.
That's the way you want it? Fine.
And we're happy to be helped. Now, what can I do for you?
Threats, huh? The stones on you. Have it your way.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Cocked head at the threat. Not frightened.
EditorData.NodeContext: A beat before the line, thoughtful, surprised.

Text.Value: Quite the opposite. I want to invest in the newest thieves' guild on the Sword Coast. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
Won't turn down free money. I've got operating costs you wouldn't believe.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Mol] takes the money given by the player. <Kealan>

Text.Value: You ready to tell me what sort of racket you're running down here?
You saved Arabella from the druids. Don't know what those bastards would have done.
You know what else costs a lot? That inspection fee.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: [Greg] set as rerecord to make sure it flows well into new following line
EditorData.NodeContext: Emphatic, implying the player needs to pay the fee.

Text.Value: Might help if you pay the inspection fee. I could take a look. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
Might help if you pay the inspection fee. I could take a look. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_2_463b0f43-5410-412d-aba3-875cf81c38ca])
Making sure we're ready to leave when the time comes.
Yes. You're taking advantage during bad times. There are words for folk like that.
You. Godsdammit, I warned you to stay away from my kids.
Still, you gave Mattis' ring back. Taught him a lesson doing it, too.
Honesty and politeness. I like that.
We're saving up for a better hideout when we get to Baldur's Gate.

EditorData.logicalname: 'Little scams? Have you heard about the Guild? You can make a living this way, in Baldur's Gate.'

Text.Value: I'm done with you. You better hope we don't have to talk again.

EditorData.logicalname: Player has pissed off Mol and she won't have anything to do with the player anymore.

Text.Value: Sounds more like a challenge than advice. Keep an eye on your pack.

EditorData.NodeContext: frustrated but with a hint of admiration. Last line is a threat to rob us in the future (pack is backpack). We just conned her, but she learned something from us.

Text.Value: You got it. Now, we done here or what?
And to make sure none of the kids on the job outside mess with you, show them this:
And now the deal's off. See you around.
Sure. Silfy probably grabbed them by mistake.

EditorData.NodeContext: Playing innocent. Silfy stole the items on purpose.

Text.Value: If you change your mind about that fee, you know where to find me.
Leave.
What're you doing down in this cave?
I don't think I'll be paying for anything. Bye for now!
What're you doing down in this cave?
Is that right? Fine, you get one more chance.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: A beat, she stares the player down.
EditorData.NodeContext: A beat, she stares the player down.

Text.Value: Foresight's the least of what we've got going, but thanks.
So what? Should we be panicking like everyone else?
I could help you get it, but my time's valuable to me.
Making sure we're ready to leave when the time comes.
Looks like some of my possessions have gone 'missing'. Again.
You're a terrible liar. We had a deal.

EditorData.NodeContext: Frustrated, disappointed - player just lied to her and she saw right through it.

Text.Value: If you don't get out of my way, I'll tear your spine out, whelp.
Then we're done here.
The bastards that killed Arabella. She was a precious little thing; like a sister to me.
I'll go tell the guards you're pushing us around. See you around, chump.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Player] attempts to replicate the hand gesture and succeeds. <Kealan>

Text.Value: You're joking, right?
And thanks for going easy on Silfy. Not many marks would've done the same.
None of yours.
I had a feeling you'd be back.
You got your junk back. Take it and get out.
I don't even know what your business is.
Mirkon says you got him out of a tight spot with some harpies. Gotta say, I'm impressed.
Ugh, get out of my head!
Count me out - I'm not getting involved.
You're right. I won't mess with any of your gang again. Promise.
Nine.
A few things are missing from your pack. Is that right?
My kids say you've been busy since you got here.
I forgot it went up a tenday ago. Anyway, pay up, and I'll see what I can do. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_2_463b0f43-5410-412d-aba3-875cf81c38ca])
Give me what's mine, or I'll rip your bloody tail off.
Still, you helped Meli get away from the adventurer.

EditorData.logicalname: Got my friend away from angry adventurer.

Text.Value: Anyway. You want to talk? Talk.
Why, you planning on telling me stealing is wrong?
Anyway. You want to talk? Talk.
I'm shy a few of my belongings - one of your associates robbed me.
Read her mind.
Still, you showed you're one of us by taking Mattis' ring. Never saw you coming, did he?
Much appreciated. Let's take a look.

EditorData.AnimationTags: *DUPE* [Mol] takes the money given by the player <Kealan>

Text.Value: Figures. Don't think you've got the stones for the job anyhow.
I didn't mean to cause trouble for your people. Should have been more careful.
Because of that, I'll give you a ten-count to leave.
I appreciate you teaching Mattis a lesson, too. Kid should be more careful with his rings.
I want to steal that big shiny idol they're all chanting at.
You saw what those bastards that run the place were doing to Arabella. Scaring the precious mite.
Now, you're going to pay for it.
Still, you got Arabella out of that mess with the druids.
You think that's funny? Fine, laugh at this.
Fine. Take it.
And I hear you have a problem.
Be careful. They look brittle as old bark, but they're vicious.
We have a plan. We're the ones who'll end up on top in the Gate. Anything else?
Pay the fee. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_2_463b0f43-5410-412d-aba3-875cf81c38ca])
You're pests, the lot of you. Stay out of my way, or else.
The important thing is to get it away from them. That ritual's gonna get us all killed.
An idol? What'll you do with something like that?
We have that in common, then. But you aren't welcome here.
Thought you might need help with something.
I appreciate you teaching Mattis a lesson, too. Kid should be more careful with his rings.
Then I'm not looking for your stuff. That was easy. Anything else?
Fine. Hope the damn thing's cursed.

EditorData.NodeContext: frustrated, but not shouting, as she's dismissed. The 'damn thing' is an idol the player stole and refused to give to her

Text.Value: And we can sell it once we get to the city. Thing like that's gotta be worth a small fortune.

EditorData.NodeContext: serious with a touch of excitement

Text.Value: Nothing piques my interest more than being told to stay away from somewhere.
I told you to leave. What happens next is your fault.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Mol] snaps her fingers to summon someone, she recieves a bag, [Someone] hands a bag to her
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: |Snaps her fingers, holding out a hand, and a bag is handed to her. She gives it to the player.|
EditorData.SFXTags: Snaps her fingers (not bones breaking, snapping her fingers to summon somebody)

Text.Value: The idol's all yours.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: The idol was moved out of the expected triggers, the player has it and gives it
EditorData.logicalname: IdolIsMissing - has it and gives it

Text.Value: Still, one of my guards said you were nice to him.

EditorData.logicalname: Was nice to kid guard during Tiefling Leader dialogue.

Text.Value: Didn't need your permission, but fine.
And we can sell it once we get to the city. Might be worth enough to pay a priest to bring Arabella back.
Don't be ridiculous. I'm not giving you anything.
Why're you running all these schemes and swindles? Risky, you know.
You scared the life out of little Silfy.
Not good enough.
See you around, maybe.
Maybe we can do something about this.
I heard you helped Meli with that locket. I owe you for that.
You've been a friend to us. Come back any time.
Nothing comes to mind. Always eager to accept donations, though.

EditorData.NodeContext: with a shrug and a smile

Text.Value: We took this off you before. Some of it's missing, feels like. But there you go.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Mol] checks the player's inventory before handing it over <Kealan>

Text.Value: Come see me in the city sometime, huh? I'll repay this and then some.
We're done here. Get lost.

EditorData.logicalname: We got nothing left to discuss and you're a wuss.

Text.Value: Pay the fee. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
I do, as a matter of fact. Revenge.
Is that a fact? I'll tell them to watch their step.
MINE. GIVE. NOW.
Mine. Now.
Ready to pay that inspection fee now? ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
What comes next is on you.
Maybe one of the kids picked up something of yours by mistake. I couldn't say.
Fine, then. What happens next is your fault.
No, no. Like this:

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Mol] repeats the hand gesture, slightly more impatiently <Kealan>

Text.Value: I'll see what I can do.
...Fine. But make any more trouble for us and you'll regret it, drow or not.

EditorData.NodeContext: A flicker of hesitation. She's just been intimidated by a drow player into letting their interference slide. She tries to mask it with a tough act.

Text.Value: Had a feeling you'd be back.
Nobody messes with my family - I'm all they've got.

Synopsis: A young woman in her early teens, crime boss, leader of the thiefling kids in the Den. She reacts to the various ways the player has treated her kids so far, and if necessary, can return items to the player that her kids have stolen.
